<br>
As I pointed out, at level 60 you should be able to walk into an area that was built for level 50 max and kick it around, it would be absurd if you couldn't.  Making it so you can NOT do so by neccessity means it is... more powerful than before.  Making monsters harder to kill makes them... more powerful. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/utargonis.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Targonis</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Sorcerer</span><br>  Posts: 638<br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/13/02 1:58 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Can game balance happen without a change to the old worl</span><hr size=1> No, my point is that the game balance will ALWAYS be broken if you don't update older zones.  <br>
<br>
If we look at EverQuest as a whole, not per expansion, then Naggy/Vox should be the least powerful, and the Ring of Scale is a complete joke compared to the dragons on Velious.  In general then, the difficulty of mobs needs to be properly adjusted so that mobs that in the game world that are comparitavely similar in power ARE similar in power, no matter when they were introduced.  If there is a need for mobs because the mobs that used to be easy are more powerful, then they should be added, or things moved around.<br>
<br>
When Kunark came out, the mobs were MUCH harder for their level compared to the old world.  Velious continued this.  Luclin was more or less even with Velious.  Now, how can you properly balance the classes unless you balance them PER EXPANSION?  For the classes to be balanced, does Verant need to say, &quot;Wizards will suck unless you have Luclin and 25AA points put into AA skills&quot;?  Wern't the mobs in Kunark designed with a certain difficulty of encounter in mind?  If future expansions trivilize the old content, then the old content should be properly balanced to compensate for this.  THAT is what I have been saying.  The thing that makes Kunark trivial isn't manaburn, it isn't the new weapons in Velious.  The thing is that the power of the players were boosted through mudflation, but the old zones wern't updated to compensate for this.  There's risk vs. reward, but if the risk is non existant for a decent reward due to expansions, that breaks the balance of the game as well.<br>
<br>
Are Velious mobs REALLY that much tougher than Kunark in a fantasy game sense, or is it just the mechanics changed to make them this way?  If the mechanics changed in one expansion, they SHOULD have changed across the board for all zones.  Once THAT is done, then you don't have to worry about stupid things like items and AA skills trivializing old content.<br>
<br>
